PREHEAT your oven for 15 minutes. PREPARE THE PAN. Spray the baking pan with cooking spray to prevent sticking. MIX THE BATTER. Pour one brownie mix and 1 1/2 teaspoons of water into a bowl. Stir until smooth. FILL THE PAN. Spoon the batter into the baking pan and spread it evenly. BAKE THE BROWNIE. Use the pan pusher to move the brownie into the oven. Bake for 8 minutes. After baking, use the pan pusher to move the brownie into the cooling chamber. Let it cool for 10 minutes. SERVE your brownie with a scoop of your favorite ice cream or a glass of cold milk.